# Harness warmup (Grace-Mar)

New Cursor threads have **no memory** of `recursion-gate`, `self-archive` (EVIDENCE), or `session-log`. Warmup fixes that.

## When to run

At the **start of a new chat** when work touches **instance state** (pipeline, RECURSION-GATE, Voice, OpenClaw handoff, `users/grace-mar/`, bootstrap continuation):

1. Run from repo root:
   ```bash
   python3 scripts/harness_warmup.py -u grace-mar
   ```
   Use `--compact` if the operator prefers one paragraph. **`--territory work-politics`** (aliases: `pol`, `wp`; legacy `wap`) = work-politics pending only; **`companion`** = Record pending only (see `recursion_gate_territory.py`).

2. **Include the command output** in your reply (paste verbatim or as a fenced markdown block) so the thread carries the same snapshot.

**Optional one-line snapshot (not a second mandatory ritual):** When the operator wants a single grounded line (e.g. “receipt” / “heartbeat line”), run `python3 scripts/harness_warmup.py -u grace-mar --receipt` (combine with `--territory` as needed). **Do not** require this as the first line of every reply — that duplicates good morning / good night (daily-warmup **A–F**) and conflicts with harness skip cases and PLAN-default in operator-style.

**One-command re-entry paste:** `python3 scripts/operator_reentry_stack.py -u grace-mar` runs handoff check, then daily warmup, then harness (add `--compact` for a shorter harness tail). Output overlaps by design; use for cold threads, not minimal noise.

**Full “good morning” stack:** When the operator says **good morning** (including **multiple times per day** for reorientation — see daily-warmup § *Multiple good mornings per day*), run that skill’s steps — including **KY-4 polling + Polymarket** per `docs/skill-work/work-politics/polling-and-markets.md` when not using **good morning light** / **minimal** — not only harness output. That skill uses **Step 1** (automated actions) then **Step 2**: fixed **A–F** menu — **A** template + boundary audit (combined when chosen), **B** repository hygiene, **C** **Daily brief** — run `generate_work_politics_daily_brief.py` + §1d Putin **only when C is chosen** (Step 1 does **not** generate the brief), **D** **RECURSION-GATE** (gate-review-pass; **no merge** without companion approval), **E** **work-dev *or* work-strategy *or* work-politics** — pick **one** lane (**companion survey** defaults under **E** / work-politics when “good morning survey”), **F** end good morning → normal workflow (not good night). **“Good morning survey”** = same stack + Step 1 flags survey; **E** defaults to survey track unless overridden. After **A–E**, **re-offer the full A–F menu** each turn until the operator chooses **F**. See `.cursor/skills/daily-warmup/SKILL.md` § *Good morning — multiple choice (A–F required)*.

**“Good night” (session end):** When the operator says **good night** or equivalent, follow `.cursor/skills/daily-warmup/SKILL.md` § **Good night** — **Step 1:** **`python3 scripts/operator_handoff_check.py -u grace-mar`** + summary paragraph; **Step 2:** fixed **A–F** menu — **A–D** are the **same** as good morning (template + boundary, repository hygiene, Daily brief, **RECURSION-GATE**); **E** = **night system pick** (integrity, Jiang closeout, survey, commit grouping, etc.); **F** = formally end night session. After **A–E**, **re-offer the full A–F menu** each turn until **F**. Do **not** substitute the full good-morning stack unless they ask for it.

## When you may skip

- Operator says they’re only editing unrelated code/docs with no gate/evidence context.
- Warmup was already pasted in this thread.
- Trivial one-line fix with no Record/pipeline involvement.

## Relation to bootstrap

`bootstrap/grace-mar-bootstrap.md` = **procedure** (what to read, work-dev, commands). Warmup = **current state** (pending candidates, last ACT, session tail). They stack: bootstrap orients; warmup grounds.

**Stewardship:** Treat warmup output as a **weather report**, not policy — policy lives in `AGENTS.md`, RECURSION-GATE, and companion-approved merges.

## Do not

- Merge or stage from warmup output — it’s read-only context.
- Treat warmup text as Record truth; canonical files remain `users/grace-mar/*.md`.
